{
	"introduction": {
		"title": "Vietnamese Adjectives: Position and Function",
		"content": [
			"Vietnamese adjectives work fundamentally differently from English adjectives in three key ways:",
			"1. POSITION: Adjectives come AFTER the noun they modify (opposite of English)",
			"2. NO COPULA: No \"to be\" verb is needed when using adjectives as predicates",
			"3. STATIVE VERBS: Vietnamese adjectives function as stative verbs - they can take tense markers and be negated directly"
		]
	},
